author: GameTimePA.com reports
title: GIRLS VOLLEYBALL: Saturday's roundup
text:
GameTimePA.com reports Posted: 10/05/2015 09:56:47 AM EDT 
WAYNESBORO WINS TWICE >> Waynesboro ran its record to 12-0 on Saturday by taking a pair of wins in the tri-match. The Maidens beat Cedar Cliff 3-1 and host Dallastown 3-0. 
The leaders in kills for the day were Brycelin Spidel (27), Olivia Fogelsonger (23) and Ciara Rosenberger (20). Jordan Stoops collected 70 assists, while Alyssa Taylor amassed 47 digs. Waynesboro 3, Dallastown 0 at Dallastown 
Waynesboro Statistics 
Kills — Brycelin Spidel 15, Olivia Fogelsonger 11, Ciara Rosenberger 8; Blocks — Spidel 6, Fogelsonger 2; Assists — Jordan Stoops 32; Digs — Alyssa Taylor 23, Kaylie Yarnell 6, Rosenberger 5; Aces — Stoops 3, Emily Bryan 2. Waynesboro 3, Cedar Cliff 1 
Sets — Way 25-18, Way 25-21, CC 21-15, Way 29-27 at Dallastown
